acme.validation.flight.identifierNumber.message = The first two letters of the identifier number must correspond to the managers's name initials

acme.validation.leg.flightNumber.message = The flight number is composed of the airline's IATA code followed by four digits (flight number letters have to be the same of airline's IATA code).

acme.validation.maintenance-record.nextInspection.message = Next inspection date must be a future date

acme.validation.service.promotionCode.message = The promotion code must match the pattern ^[A-Z]{4}-[0-9]{2}$, and its last two characters must match current year last two digits

acme.validation.customer.identifier.syntax.message = The customer identifier first two or three letters must correspond to their initials

acme.validation.customer.identifier.unique.message = The customer identifier must be unique

acme.validation.technician.licenseNumber.message = The first two letters of the license number must correspond to the technician's initials

acme.validation.aircraft.registration-number-duplicated.message  = The registraton number is already in use

acme.validation.flight-crew-member.employee-code-duplicated.message = The employee code is already in use
acme.validation.flight-crew-member.employee-code-invalid-format.message = The employee code must match the pattern ^[A-Z]{2,3}\\d{6}$
acme.validation.flight-crew-member.employee-code-not-matching-initials.message = The first two letters of the employee code must match the initials of the member

acme.validation.log.registration-moment.message = The log registration moment must occur after the leg finishes.